Analyze this memory leak in a React application. The component unmounts but the WebSocket connection stays open and keeps updating state. Show the fix and explain the React lifecycle implications.
```jsx
function LiveFeed({ url }) {
  const [data, setData] = useState([]);
  useEffect(() => {
    const ws = new WebSocket(url);
    ws.onmessage = (e) => setData(prev => [...prev, JSON.parse(e.data)]);
  }, [url]);
  return <div>{data.map(d => <Item key={d.id} {...d} />)}</div>;
}
```

